WorkItem.Description:
Hi,

__Version: 0.9.5 Beta__

The following:

```TypeScript
window.onerror = (message:any, source:string, line:number) => {
    console.log(message);
};
```

fails to compile with 

error TS2012: Build: Cannot convert '(message: any, source: string, line: number) => void' to 'ErrorEventHandler'

The definition in Lib.d.ts is expecting an `ErrorEventHandler`, but really it should be a function reference. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/GlobalEventHandlers.onerror).
